with the following structure:

What:		/sys/devices/platform/gdmc_dhub/*/baudrate
Date:		January 2024
KernelVersion:	6.1.57-android14-11
Description:
		Query or set the UART Baudrate.  Subsystem UART baudrates
		are generally set at compile time in the subsystem's firmware.
		The DHUB UART baudrate settings are configured to match the
		subsystem baudrate by the device bootloader at boot.  This
		sysfs entry could be used to override the bootloader setting,
		if required (for example, if a subsystem firmware provides an
		out-of-band means to change its UART baudrate).

What:		/sys/devices/platform/gdmc_dhub/*/virt_en
Date:		January 2024
KernelVersion:	6.1.57-android14-11
Description:
		Query or set whether subsytem UART is enabled for virtualization.
		When a subsystem UART is enabled for virtualization, its UART
		Tx/Rx signals are disconnected from any dedicated UART pins on the
		SoC, and instead plumbed through the DHUB.  The UART data is
		packetized and sent through the multiplexed data stream over the
		devices SBU lines to a host over the device's debug USB port.
		A debugging dongle (e.g. Blammo) and associated host drivers are
		required to convert the SBU signals into a USB / virtual-UART
		terminal console on the host.  A user-space tool is also required
		to de-multiplex the DHUB datastream into individual subsystem UART
		data streams.
